articles.title: Archive
articles.contents:
Here is an archive of R cheatsheets and presentations I made when I
was a postbacc at the University of Michigan. The presentations will
download as a .pptx file.
Most of the cheatsheets are old and were made when I didn’t know R as
well as I do now, but I still like them. I might try to make updated
versions in the future.

articles.title: Research
articles.contents:
As an undergraduate at Smith College, I was a member of Dr. Nnamdi
Pole’s lab. I completed my senior thesis on
facial expressivity, emotional coherence, and PTSD in a psychotherapy
case study.
After graduating, I joined Dr. Christoper Monk’s
lab as a postbacc lab manager and coordinated study efforts with the
Study
of Adolescent Neural Development (SAND), a substudy of the Fragile Families and Child
Wellbeing Study. I am currently writing a paper on ventral striatum
connectivity and reward processing in the SAND sample; we hope to submit
it to Brain Research soon.
I joined The Ohio State University’s clinical psychology program in
Fall 2020. I completed my firstyear project on
automated facial expression coding in mother-daughter dyads with
Nathaniel Haines.
Broadly speaking, I am interested in affective science and emotion
regulation in clinical populations. I am happiest when working with big
datasets that need carpentry and visualization. Please contact me via
email or Twitter if you
are interested in collaboration.
